# 📄 ChallengeService.java — README

**Package:** `services`
**Type:** `public class`
**Project:** SolveStack – Open Innovation Collaboration Platform

---

## 📌 What Is This File?

`ChallengeService.java` is the **service layer** responsible for all platform-wide challenge operations. While `Company.java` owns and manages challenges that *belong to it*, `ChallengeService` maintains a **master registry** of every challenge across all companies on the platform.

Think of it like this: `Company` is the owner of a challenge, but `ChallengeService` is the platform administrator that keeps track of everything globally — approvals, searches, evaluator assignments, and registry management.

---

## 🎯 Purpose & Responsibility

| Responsibility | Method |
|---|---|
| Create and register a new challenge | `createChallenge(...)` |
| Delete a challenge from the platform | `deleteChallenge(...)` |
| Fetch all challenges (all statuses) | `getAllChallenges()` |
| Fetch only open/available challenges | `getOpenChallenges()` |
| Search by keyword in title or description | `searchChallenges(String keyword)` |
| Filter challenges by status | `filterByStatus(String status)` |
| Assign an evaluator to a challenge | `assignEvaluator(...)` |
| Approve a pending challenge (Admin action) | `approveChallenge(String id)` |
| Look up a challenge by its ID | `getChallengeById(String id)` |
| Print a full platform challenge report | `printAllChallenges()` |

